title: Natalie Bassingthwaighte struggles with her heaving trolley of luggage
text:
She's been in the spotlight for close to 17 years.

So you'd think Natalie Bassingthwaighte would have an assistant or two on hand.

But on Tuesday, the 44-year-old singer and actress proved she was just like the rest of us when she was spotted pushing a trolley of what looked to be all her worldly possessions through Sydney Airport, before screeching to a mate: 'How much stuff do I have?'

All glammed up: On Tuesday, Natalie Bassingthwaighte (pictured) was spotted pushing a trolley of what looked to be all her worldly possessions through Sydney airport

Natalie's staggering mountain of bags included one extra large black carrier, a matching large and medium blue suitcase and a black carry-on for all her irreplaceable jewellery and valuables.

In the footage, a Qantas representative can be seen happily shepherding the petite A-list performer through the terminal, even directing an elderly woman to be cautious of Nat's oncoming semi trailer of short-haul knick knacks.

In the video, the former So You Think You Can Dance host is heard muttering apologies for her heavy load as she snaked haphazardly through the terminal.

'How much stuff do I have?' Natalie screeched to a mate, dressed in all-black, who stepped in to help out.

Bag lady: Natalie staggering mountain of bags included one extra large black carrier, a matching large and medium blue suitcase and a black carry-on for all her irreplaceable jewellery and valuables

Beep beep, coming through! In the footage, a Qantas representative can be seen happily shepherding the petite A-list performer through the terminal

Coffee? Tea? Nat could barely see over her pile of short-haul knick knacks, which made steering a nightmare

The former Rogue Traders front woman cut a casual figure in a grey tank top, a pair of well-worn blue jeans and white trainers.

She accessorised her dressed-down flying attire with a shirt tied around her waist, an on-trend black belt bag and a pair of trusty sunglasses on her tied back blonde locks to help her evade prying eyes.

Natalie lives in Melbourne with her husband Cameron McGlinchey, daughter Harper, eight and son Hendrix, five.

She's built for comfort: The former Rogue Traders front woman cut a casual figure in a grey tank top, a pair of well-worn blue jeans and a pair of white trainers

Rescue me! 'How much stuff do I have?' Natalie screeched to a mate, dressed in all-black (pictured), who stepped in to help out

In a lengthy Instagram post recently, the former Neighbours star said she would rather be 'more present' with her two children than chase 'likes' on social media.

'It doesn't matter how many followers you have or how many likes you have... I would love for the likes and dislikes to stop,' said Natalie.

'We need to start living! Living day to day. Being present... and stop worrying what people think of us and stop comparing ourselves to people in Instagram.'
description: She's been in the spotlight for close to 17 years.
authors: Shannon Shipley For Daily Mail Australia
